.TH "fsl_ssi_set_bclk" 9 "fsl_ssi_set_bclk" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fsl_ssi_set_bclk \- Configure Digital Audio Interface bit clock
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fsl_ssi_set_bclk
.BI "(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream "  ","
.BI "struct snd_soc_dai *dai "  ","
.BI "struct snd_pcm_hw_params *hw_params "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "substream" 12
ASoC substream
.IP "dai" 12
pointer to DAI
.IP "hw_params" 12
pointers to hw_params
.SH "NOTES"
This function can be only called when using SSI as DAI master
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Quick instruction for parameters:
freq: Output BCLK frequency = samplerate * slots * slot_width
(In 2-channel I2S Master mode, slot_width is fixed 32)
